In this statement, President Obama thanks Secretary Steven Chu for his service to the American people. He acknowledges Chu's expertise as a Nobel Prize-winning scientist and praises his understanding of the urgent challenge of climate change and the economic opportunities in clean energy. The President highlights the achievements during Chu's time as Secretary, including doubling the use of renewable energy, reducing dependence on foreign oil, and positioning the country to lead the global race for clean energy jobs. Obama expresses gratitude for Chu's support of engineers and entrepreneurs pursuing innovative energy solutions. The President concludes by wishing Chu well in his future endeavors.